<subSubSection id="DCABB523F7352CF8F6D8438626BEE199" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3A86125D453A779CD2546122735E58FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="596ADCF92CD740946202644DD7E32433" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is named after &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="1760AFA982B4867398E664CB8A5B4C78" authorityName="Liao &amp; Terayama &amp; Eguchi" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristepyris seqalu" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seqalu">Pristepyris seqalu</taxonomicName>
&quot;, an aboriginal people who live primarily in Hengchen Township in Taiwan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EC5E957A6F5E3F4988E73E68C4AD2767" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="taxonomic remarks">
<paragraph id="B729FEC514CF759D3243552B8E870860" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Taxonomic remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="260ED6DD75BAC770C7368ED1C0EC5969" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is most similar in general appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="683A72E6FDB9CA68B13A622A8FB81098" genus="P." lsidName="P. rugulosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rugulosus">
<emphasis id="40A17D994CE6A3B1B48F4B9BE6FA4FC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. rugulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D07F5FA3B0B7E84972AD2BAC79556878" author="Terayama, M" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="81 - 86" refId="B35" refString="Terayama, M, Xu, ZF, He, JH, 2002. Three new species of the genus Acrepyris Kieffer, 1905 (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae) from China. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 8: 81 - 86" title="Three new species of the genus Acrepyris Kieffer, 1905 (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae) from China." volume="8" year="2002">Terayama et al. 2002</bibRefCitation>
) among the named species known from East and Southeast Asia. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="53C2E136A3D639DA917D61C495B3DB49" author="Terayama, M" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="81 - 86" refId="B35" refString="Terayama, M, Xu, ZF, He, JH, 2002. Three new species of the genus Acrepyris Kieffer, 1905 (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae) from China. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 8: 81 - 86" title="Three new species of the genus Acrepyris Kieffer, 1905 (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae) from China." volume="8" year="2002">Terayama et al. (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, posterior transverse margin of metapectal-propodeal complex is distinct in 
<taxonomicName id="91E6E766FA4FC84482CA4E0F7BEC6224" genus="P." lsidName="P. rugulosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rugulosus">
<emphasis id="EB45365BE3B8187C82080A650B4D858A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. rugulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but indistinct in 
<taxonomicName id="2A422A22AD24384DCE18F38C4E8548EF" genus="P." lsidName="P. seqalu" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="seqalu">
<emphasis id="195510CCA4C5AF25A90651568B72D993" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. seqalu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.; apical margin of hypopygium is incurved fully in 
<taxonomicName id="80F709C32377855C428C55F4FB7BB62B" genus="P." lsidName="P. rugulosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rugulosus">
<emphasis id="0ACE0D3624AFCB4295CB1750B757F7E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. rugulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but only incurved medially in 
<taxonomicName id="759BB374027C7056A1A603CF88B7C135" genus="P." lsidName="P. seqalu" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="seqalu">
<emphasis id="777E883834F8D40C6F9E387F39F4BFF9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. seqalu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.; apical lobe of aedeagus in lateral view is relatively small and narrow in 
<taxonomicName id="2FF52C7A0885F85CC4F512C2D1DA8943" genus="P." lsidName="P. rugulosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rugulosus">
<emphasis id="73B462D7F16A0CF815378DACC1FA6F25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. rugulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but relatively well-developed, broad and lobate in 
<taxonomicName id="75F789AB14938C9419AC1C203E6D8147" genus="P." lsidName="P. seqalu" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="seqalu">
<emphasis id="28F2C5B4C85E99316714709404C01A1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. seqalu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
